cs.ET, cs.AI, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.EM

Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The paper discusses electronic-design-automation (EDA) tools which are commonly used in embedded systems design. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed machine learning framework using gradient boost regressor (GBR) model falls under the category of AI. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper discusses customized routing optimizations which are a key aspect of hardware architecture design. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses how to achieve better design quality through optimization, which is a key aspect of systems and control. 
- cs.EM (Electromagnetics): The paper discusses timing improvement which is related to signal propagation and electromagnetic effects in circuits.
